{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/how-to-fix-python-ssl-certificate-verify-failed/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"itsopensource"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"cdd2b292-7443-57a3-a853-c9ea5f947d9d","excerpt":"Recently after upgrading the python version to , I started getting this error every time I am running any python script. The reason behind this is Python 3.6 onâ€¦","html":"<p>Recently after upgrading the python version to <code class=\"language-text\">3.6</code>, I started getting this error every time I am running any python script.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> certificate verify failed <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>_ssl.c:726<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The reason behind this is Python 3.6 on macOS uses an embedded version of OpenSSL, which does not use the system certificate store. More information <a href=\"https://bugs.python.org/issue28150\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Quick fix for this problem on macOS is to open Finder and double-clicking <code class=\"language-text\">Install Certificates.command</code></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 311px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/21603b710f58cb7b25a20e0b38499ee5/ffa0f/1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 60.810810810810814%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/21603b710f58cb7b25a20e0b38499ee5/ffa0f/1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/21603b710f58cb7b25a20e0b38499ee5/12f09/1.png 148w,\n/static/21603b710f58cb7b25a20e0b38499ee5/e4a3f/1.png 295w,\n/static/21603b710f58cb7b25a20e0b38499ee5/ffa0f/1.png 311w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 311px) 100vw, 311px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Or you can do this via terminal by:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">open</span> /Applications/Python<span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span> <span class=\"token number\">3.6</span>/Install<span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span> Certificates.command</code></pre></div>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to fix Python SSL CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED","tags":["python","ssl","how-to"],"date":"December 12, 2019","description":null,"author":"shivam","featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/how-to-fix-python-ssl-certificate-verify-failed/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-setup-irc-and-irc-bouncer/"},"frontmatter":{"author":"shivam","tags":["irc","bouncer","how-to"],"title":"How to setup IRC and IRC bouncer"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/offline-caching-with-serviceworkers/"},"frontmatter":{"author":"trishul","tags":["PWA","servcieworkers","javascript"],"title":"Offline caching with serviceworkers"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["4268877247","764694655"],"slicesMap":{}}